The President's Weekly Address, released on April 7, 2017, highlights the progress made by the administration in the first 11 weeks. The address emphasizes the optimism expressed by domestic manufacturers and the focus on jobs, opportunity, safety, and security. The President discusses the efforts made to secure the border, highlighting a 64% reduction in illegal immigration on the southern border. The administration is also conducting enforcement actions to remove dangerous criminal aliens from society. The President mentions recent arrests of criminal aliens involved in various crimes. The address also touches on the efforts to strengthen alliances and improve relationships with other nations, including hosting the President of Egypt, the King of Jordan, and a summit with President Xi of China. The President emphasizes the importance of advocating for the national interests of the United States and ensuring that decisions serve the safety and security of American citizens. The address concludes with a focus on a future of peace, safety, and prosperity for the country.